==English==
===Etymology===
From Punjabi [[ਗੁਰਮੁਖੀ]], commonly translated as "from the Mouth of the Guru", since it was standardised by Guru Angad Dev in the 16th century.
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Gurmukhī'''

# An [[abugida]] [[script]], or writing system, designed for writing the [[Punjabi]] language. It has been adapted to write other languages, such as [[Braj Bhasha]], [[Hindi]], [[Sanskrit]] and [[Sindhi]].

